ring model (work is in progress for\nmore complex scattering models). We found that the ellipsoids by photometry\ninversion are closely similar to the best-fitting ellipsoids of the simulated\ncomplex shapes and that the error on the asteroid volume (relative to a complex\nshape) is generally low, usually around $10\\%$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Mar 2019 15:10:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-01"}
